description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a highly motivated and enthusiastic individual to join the ENT administration team. You will need to provide an efficient and comprehensive secretarial service and should have previous secretarial and administrative experience. Excellent organisational skills are required as is the ability to work under pressure, prioritise workloads and work to deadlines.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellent communication skills are required and the post holder will need to have the ability to liaise with staff at all levels and work effectively and efficiently as part of a team. This is a busy role and the post holder will need to have a flexible approach to work and be able to use their own initiative.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is a Full Time post working 37.5 hours per week.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Proposed Interview Date: Week beginning Monday 16th November 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Claire Penna - Clinical Administration Lead on Tel: 07919572386. Or email: claire.penna@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
